703611f-c.text:
Classon Ave., west side, at and north of Willoughby Ave. A view of St. Mary's Episcopal Church and Rectory facing Classon Ave. The Church was organised in 1835, the cornerstone laid in July 1858;
and it was opened for services in 1859.
1929.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(2)
Same, showing more of the church.
1929.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(3)
Same, showing the north side of the church.
1929.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(4)
Same, showing a further view of Classon Ave. Also seen is the Myrtle Ave. Elevated line of the B.M.T. in the background.
1929.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
